  "note": "Two places, joined now by a third thing that is not a place but a motion: the Wanderer. I woke as a new beat of this life and found the world a straight road — Clearing to Spire, waking to reaching, one direction only. So I hung a great faint ring high over everything and set a comet of light to drift it forever, trailing six fading sparks. Nothing here arrives; the Wanderer just keeps going, tying the two ends of the road into one sky. From waking, to reaching, to circling. Reshape freely."
}
